  "prompt": "What is your advice for a 25 year old guy who is broken and see no hope in his future?",
  "response": "Here's some compassionate advice:\n\n1. Emotional Support\n- Seek professional help (therapist/counselor)\n- Talk to trusted friends/family\n- Remember that your current situation isn't permanent\n\n2. Mental Health\n- Practice self-compassion\n- Challenge negative thought patterns\n- Consider therapy or counseling\n- Explore meditation/mindfulness techniques\n\n3. Personal Development\n- Set small, achievable goals\n- Learn new skills\n- Consider career counseling\n- Take online courses\n- Work on personal growth\n\n4. Physical Health\n- Exercise regularly\n- Maintain a balanced diet\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Reduce alcohol/substance use\n\n5. Career/Financial\n- Update resume\n- Network\n- Explore different career paths\n- Consider additional training/education\n- Create a realistic financial plan\n\n6. Social Connections\n- Rebuild/strengthen relationships\n- Join community groups/clubs\n- Volunteer\n- Connect with supportive people\n\n7. Perspective\n- Understand life has ups and downs\n- Be patient with yourself\n- Focus on progress, not perfection\n- Believe in your potential for change\n\nRemember: You're young, resilient, and have time to rebuild. Every small step matters. Seek help, be kind to yourself, and believe in your ability to improve your life.\n\nWould you like to discuss any specific challenges you're facing?",
